                {# NOTE/TODO: optional caption but below the swiper, individually #}
                {% if coverPhoto.figcaption is defined and coverPhoto.figcaption !== '' %}
                  <figcaption class="mt-spacer-1">{{ coverPhoto.figcaption }}</figcaption>
                {% endif %}
              </figure>
            </div>
            <div class="monz-col-4">
              <h1 class="font-serif">{{ title }}</h1>
              <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-spacer-3 mt-0">{{ excerpt }}</p>
              <div class="lg:grid lg:grid-cols-4 lg:gap-x-spacer-2 mb-spacer-2">
                <a href="{{ newsbarLinkHref }}" class="link-underline block bg-primary uppercase p-spacer-1 text-left text-spacer-1 text-body leading-none">Watch --&gt;</a>
              </div>

              {% block abstract %}
                {# NOTE: placeholder for Abstract #}
              {% endblock %}

              {% if projectDetails %}
                <dl class="mt-spacer-4">
                  {% for key, value in projectDetails %}
                    <dt class="clear-left float-left pr-spacer-1/2">{{ key }}:</dt>
                    <dd>{{ value }}</dd>
                  {% endfor %}
                </dl>
              {% endif %}
            </div>

            <div class="monz-col-6">
              <h2 class="font-serif normal-case mb-spacer-3 mt-spacer-2">Reviews</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="monz-col-4 mb-spacer-2">
              <h3>Critique by Sebastian Höglinger, translated by Lisa Rosenblatt:</h3>
              <p>“Caught in the wake of an animated pipe system, The Construction of ANSTALT3000 leads down to the limbo of wrong-headed hyper-fiction and even further to the borders of imagination, taken literally – quasi into a latently obscene in-between world defined by counter- and meta-logics. Sounds dodgy? Well, it is: dodgy and frantically clever.</p>
              <p>In fragile, billowing, animated scenes, hybrid creatures featuring rather awkward forms confront themselves and their audience with at times bizarrely humorous word, text, and body mutations. God is fabricated as a little digital heap of misery – for the sole purpose of refuting his existence – surroundings and beings deform with a consistent, level timing and in their structure recall both popular gaming scenes and the skit style of early film comedies.</p>
              <p>Munz´s only seemingly naïve asylum and its inhabitants, highly complex in their consistent concentration, tell of the process in the title; construction and throwing over: of meanings, spaces, and no least, conventions of communication in the 'digital era'. They thereby have an unmistakable affinity to David O´Reilly´s grandly overflowing cinematic and imaginative worlds. By means of parody (and to serve it), an – at times error affirming – pendant is offered to the commercial-tidy-aesthetics of conventional 3D animation. A universe that pleasurably continues to give birth to itself from its own intrinsic logic and which Munz ends at the physical fusion with already introduced characters – a refreshing symbol of constructed non-perfection, similar to a 'boss' in classical arcade console adventures."</p>
            </div>
            <div class="monz-col-2">
              <div class="monz-tile break-inside-avoid-column mb-spacer-2">
                <button type="button" data-modal-target="modal-layout-columns-2-4" data-modal-toggle="modal-layout-columns-2-4" class="w-full text-left">
                  <figure>
                    <div class="h-spacer-14 bg-light mb-spacer-1">
                      {# NOTE: example of setting an dynamic pictureObject before including components/picture-example.njk #}
                      {% set pictureObject = coverPhoto %}
                      {% include "components/picture-example.njk" %}
                    </div>
                    <figcaption>Fig. 1.1: Image Caption of this image that says something (Copyright © Eman Ali, 2022)</figcaption>
                  </figure>
                </button>
              </div>

              <div class="monz-tile break-inside-avoid-column mb-spacer-2">
                <button type="button" data-modal-target="modal-layout-columns-2-4" data-modal-toggle="modal-layout-columns-2-4" class="w-full text-left">
                  <figure>
                    <div class="h-spacer-14 bg-light mb-spacer-1">
                      {# NOTE: example of setting an dynamic pictureObject before including components/picture-example.njk #}
                      {% set pictureObject = coverPhoto %}
                      {% include "components/picture-example.njk" %}
                    </div>
                    <figcaption>Fig. 1.1: Image Caption of this image that says something (Copyright © Eman Ali, 2022)</figcaption>
                  </figure>
                </button>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        {# NOTE: full width/edge-to-edge cover photo markup "components/cover-photo-edge-to-edge-example.njk" #}
        <figure class="mb-spacer-3">
          <div class="bg-success relative">
            <div class="absolute top-0 bottom-0 left-0 right-0">
